rror was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Lucy Frazer       Share       As my right hon. Friend implies, every parent who separates wants to continue to have contact with their child. I was pleased to talk about this issue with him and my hon. Friend the Member for North West Leicestershire (Andrew Bridgen). I have taken up their proposal and spoken about it with the president of the family division, as well as with a number of organisations that deal with children and legal representatives in the family courts. I should say that they all have differing perspectives, but we are looking at this matter very closely.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Stephanie Peacock (Barnsley East) (Lab)       Share       It is now two years since the Government made a commitment to ban perpetrators from cross-examining victims of domestic abuse in family courts, which the Minister has just mentioned, but when will she actually follow through on that and finally act on this issue?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Lucy Frazer       Share       We will follow through on this issue, which is a Government priority—     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Stephanie Peacock       Share       But when?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Lucy Frazer       Share       It will be in a Bill as soon as legislation and the parliamentary timetable allow.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This c